  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "title-cell",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "title-cell"
      },
      "source": [
        "# 🦅 Horus-OSINT: Fine-Tuning Llama-3-8B-Instruct\n",
        "**CISC 886 – Cloud Computing | Queen's University**\n",
        "\n",
        "**Group:** 23\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook fine-tunes `Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct` on the processed GTD+GDELT OSINT dataset\n",
        "using **Unsloth** (2x faster training) and **QLoRA** (4-bit, PEFT) as recommended by the course resource guide.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Pipeline:\n",
        "1. Install Unsloth + dependencies\n",
        "2. Load base model in 4-bit quantization\n",
        "3. Apply LoRA adapters (PEFT)\n",
        "4. Load processed JSONL data from S3\n",
        "5. Train with SFTTrainer\n",
        "6. Compare base vs fine-tuned responses\n",
        "7. Export to GGUF → upload to S3 for EC2 deployment\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "> ⚠️ **Runtime:** Set to `T4 GPU` in Google Colab (Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "section-1-md",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "section-1-md"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Section 1 — Install Dependencies"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "install-deps",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "install-deps",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "625d693d-c858-4dc7-ed63-691e3724002d"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "  Installing build dependencies ... \u001b[?25l\u001b[?25hdone\n",
            "  Getting requirements to build wheel ... \u001b[?25l\u001b[?25hdone\n",
            "  Preparing metadata (pyproject.toml) ... \u001b[?25l\u001b[?25hdone\n",
            "✅ Dependencies installed successfully!\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Install Unsloth and latest HuggingFace stack cleanly\n",
        "!pip install \"unsloth[colab-new] @ git+https://github.com/unslothai/unsloth.git\" -q\n",
        "!pip install trl peft accelerate bitsandbytes -q\n",
        "!pip install boto3 -q\n",
        "print(\"✅ Dependencies installed successfully!\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "verify-gpu",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "verify-gpu",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "d8cafb91-2e1d-446d-d0a0-6be25c9c6e0f"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "✅ GPU detected: Tesla T4\n",
            "   VRAM available: 15.6 GB\n",
            "   CUDA version:   12.8\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Verify GPU is available — required for training\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "\n",
        "if not torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
        "    raise RuntimeError(\"❌ No GPU detected! Go to Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU\")\n",
        "\n",
        "gpu_name = torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)\n",
        "vram_gb  = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9\n",
        "print(f\"✅ GPU detected: {gpu_name}\")\n",
        "print(f\"   VRAM available: {vram_gb:.1f} GB\")\n",
        "print(f\"   CUDA version:   {torch.version.cuda}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "section-2-md",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "section-2-md"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Section 2 — Configuration\n",
        "All project-wide constants are defined here. Edit only this cell to adapt the notebook."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "config",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "config",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "cb19e21e-8774-427b-a82a-8b944dd7131f"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "✅ Configuration loaded.\n",
            "   S3 Bucket: s3://horus-25bbdf-g23-bucket\n",
            "   Model:     unsloth/llama-3-8b-Instruct-bnb-4bit\n",
            "   S3 train:  s3://horus-25bbdf-g23-bucket/processed/train.jsonl\n",
            "   S3 model:  s3://horus-25bbdf-g23-bucket/models/horus-llama3-osint-Q4_K_M.gguf\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
        "#  PROJECT CONFIGURATION  —  edit here only\n",
        "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
        "\n",
        "NETID          = \"25bbdf-g23\"\n",
        "S3_BUCKET      = f\"horus-{NETID}-bucket\"\n",
        "AWS_REGION     = \"us-east-1\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# S3 keys — PySpark writes partitioned folders; we target the folder root\n",
        "S3_TRAIN_PREFIX = \"processed/train.jsonl\"\n",
        "S3_DATA_KEY     = S3_TRAIN_PREFIX\n",
        "S3_MODEL_KEY    = \"models/horus-llama3-osint-Q4_K_M.gguf\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Model — Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct from Unsloth's optimized hub\n",
        "BASE_MODEL = \"unsloth/llama-3-8b-Instruct-bnb-4bit\"\n",
        "MODEL_NAME     = \"horus-llama3-osint\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
        "#  HYPERPARAMETERS  (documented in report)\n",
        "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
        "LORA_R         = 16      # LoRA rank — balances VRAM vs expressive power\n",
        "LORA_ALPHA     = 32      # Scaling factor = 2 × rank (standard practice)\n",
        "LORA_DROPOUT   = 0.05    # Small dropout for regularisation\n",
        "LEARNING_RATE  = 2e-4    # Stable starting point for PEFT with AdamW\n",
        "BATCH_SIZE     = 2       # Optimised for T4 16GB VRAM\n",
        "GRAD_ACCUM     = 4       # Effective batch = 2×4 = 8 for stable gradients\n",
        "MAX_STEPS      = 500     # Sufficient to adapt formatting to OSINT domain\n",
        "MAX_SEQ_LEN    = 2048    # Max token length per sample\n",
        "OPTIMIZER      = \"adamw_8bit\"  # Memory-efficient optimizer from Unsloth\n",
        "WARMUP_STEPS   = 50      # Gradual LR warm-up to prevent instability\n",
        "LR_SCHEDULER   = \"cosine\"     # Smooth LR decay over training\n",
        "SEED           = 42\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✅ Configuration loaded.\")\n",
        "print(f\"   S3 Bucket: s3://{S3_BUCKET}\")\n",
        "print(f\"   Model:     {BASE_MODEL}\")\n",
        "print(f\"   S3 train:  s3://{S3_BUCKET}/{S3_DATA_KEY}\")\n",
        "print(f\"   S3 model:  s3://{S3_BUCKET}/{S3_MODEL_KEY}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "section-3-md",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "section-3-md"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Section 3 — Load Base Model with 4-bit Quantization\n",
        "We use `FastLanguageModel` from Unsloth which wraps HuggingFace and applies\n",
        "optimised CUDA kernels. Loading in 4-bit (QLoRA) cuts VRAM from ~16 GB to ~6 GB."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "load-model",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "load-model",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 275,
          "referenced_widgets": [
            "ab2c4203541548178ca83df7a8ca9f2f",
            "07c55bc0b8a94eeea905a5913ccfc70c",
            "3a676cb78ff643fcb5c2e62783fee904",
            "6aadd6b44af64546b024a46d41d56239",
            "512a6dec165b4eef954b3a3c8cf150e0",
            "291116181f8647d7bf4066fd419d39c0",
            "bb3b3b3811684613bdf32df76994d3e7",
            "fefe1d8fdc2a4fe4add3d0e27a10980b",
            "6caf8a81fba8448c9d09c35e58a6dfb5",
            "1740d7830efe41db92d2b2708b3cad5f",
            "9d14c9498748401684da3767d03a10c1"
          ]
        },
        "outputId": "f2e86d62-0274-4bd5-a16e-45dc2b0844ac"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
